When the entrant of the fishing industry had Mexico and The Salvador as their cores, Panama has the best deep water port called Panama Canal. Panama decided to make use of the canal as their asset after the conquest of Panama from Colombia. The acquisition of Panama from Colombia brought about the rebranding of Panama as “Panama” from “Colombo”. Canal was opened to the world for navigation in 1914 (Randalls,2011).

The entrance of fishing industry in Panama resulted to the elimination of local business and brought forth generation of small workplaces. The Canal opened a countless opportunities for people from other bordering towns as a sign of rebranding of Panama. Considering the position of canal undertaken by Panama, it demonstrated that environment is a central driver of development. Industry within an area determines interactions between environment and commercial assets. There exist a crucial relationship between the development of an area and its features. Panama’s waterways serve as an easy angle of movement of people and goods during their operation. This is a factor that contributed towards the development of Panama (Randalls,2011).

Overpopulation has become a core warning indicator to a community. There are wide connections between human activities and environmental degradation that continues to affect Panama’s waterways. Alongside fishing sector, Panama has been negatively impacted with illegal dumping particularly after the institution of the Canal.
